<% content_for :title, "Get SimLink" %>

<div class="text-center mt-6 mb-8">
  <div class="mx-auto w-16 h-16 rounded-2xl bg-primary flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
    <span class="text-white text-2xl">💬</span>
  </div>
  <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-1">SimLink</h1>
  <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Give your AI agents the power to send & receive SMS through your phone.</p>
</div>

<!-- Download -->
<%= link_to apk_download_path, download: "simlink.apk",
      class: "block text-center rounded-xl bg-primary hover:bg-primary-light text-white font-semibold px-4 py-3.5 mb-2" do %>
  ⬇ Download the Android app (.apk)
<% end %>
<p class="text-center text-xs text-gray-400 mb-6">
  Android only · sideloaded · ~18&nbsp;MB. iOS can't send SMS, so there's no iOS app.
</p>

<!-- Use a spare phone -->
<div class="rounded-xl bg-rose-50 border border-rose-200 p-3 text-sm text-rose-800 mb-8">
  <strong>Use a spare phone.</strong> Install this on an old/secondary Android device with a prepaid
  SIM — not the personal phone you use every day. It's a sideloaded app and hasn't been tested across
  every phone, so treat it as experimental.
</div>

<!-- Steps -->
<ol class="space-y-3 mb-6">
  <%= render "downloads/step", n: 1, title: "Install on a spare Android phone",
        body: "Open the downloaded .apk and tap Install. If Android warns about installing from an unknown source, allow it for your browser or Files app, then continue." %>
  <%= render "downloads/step", n: 2, title: "Open SimLink & sign in",
        body: "Create your account (or sign in) right in the app." %>
  <%= render "downloads/step", n: 3, title: "Connect your phone & grant SMS permission",
        body: "Tap “Connect phone” and allow SMS + phone permissions so SimLink can text on your behalf. If Android refuses, see the box below." %>
  <%= render "downloads/step", n: 4, title: "Share a SIM & connect an agent",
        body: "Pick the SIM to share, create a token, and paste the MCP URL into ChatGPT, Claude, or any agent." %>
</ol>

<!-- Troubleshooting: SMS permission denied -->
<div class="rounded-xl bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 p-3 text-sm text-amber-800 mb-8">
  <p class="font-semibold mb-1">Saw “App was denied access to SMS”?</p>
  <p class="mb-2">
    Android treats SMS as a restricted permission and auto-blocks it for sideloaded apps (Xiaomi/MIUI,
    Samsung and Android&nbsp;13+ are the strictest). You have to grant it by hand — it can take some hunting:
  </p>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-1">
    <li>Open <strong>Settings → Apps → SimLink → Permissions → SMS</strong> and set it to <strong>Allow</strong>.</li>
    <li>On Android&nbsp;13+, if SMS is greyed out, open the app's info page, tap the <strong>⋮</strong> menu (top-right) and choose <strong>“Allow restricted settings”</strong> first.</li>
    <li>On Xiaomi/MIUI it's buried deeper — try <strong>Settings → Apps → Manage apps → SimLink → Permissions</strong>, and also check <em>Autostart</em> / <em>Other permissions</em>. Expect some clicking around.</li>
  </ol>
  <p class="mt-2">Then reopen SimLink and sign in again.</p>
</div>

<div class="rounded-xl bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 p-3 text-sm text-amber-800 mb-8">
  <strong>Heads up:</strong> sending automated texts from a personal SIM can be rate-limited by your
  carrier. Keep volumes low. Texts are sent from <em>your</em> number.
</div>

<p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500">
  Already installed? Open the SimLink app to continue. ·
  <%= link_to "Manage account", new_session_path, class: "text-primary underline" %>
</p>
